{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_queenofspades_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608750/1958042301/0690.xml":{"full_text":"B-20\nTHE EVENING STAR. Washington. D. C.\nWFDNXrOAS. aran \u00abl. iMa\nWarm Spell Swamps\nAir-Conditioner Firms\nBy WILLIAM A. Ml 1.1.1 N\nStar Bull Writer\nWashington's recent hot weather mused aii-mnduinning\nservicemen to be swamped with calls. William O. Hills, man\naging director. Electilc Institute of Washington, said today.\nAnd aales of new units also stepped up.\nMr. Hills said Washington a large potential market for air\nconditioning, the growing business and the limited number of\nair conditioning servicemen\navailable have prompted the\nInstitute to Join In a special\ntraining program. In co-opera\ntion with the District Board of\nEducation this will start In\nthe fall at the Chamberlain\nVocational High School.\nThe course will run two\nnishts a week for 15 weeks for\ntwo to three hours each night.\nAs one group Is graduated, an\nother 15-week course will begin.\nMr. Hills said.\n\"We are trying to get the\nyoung men coming out of high\nschool to get Into this line of\nwork.\u201d he declared.\n1957 Sales Rise\nWhile March figures are not\nyet available. Mr. Hills said\nduring January and February\nthis year 2.579 window air-con\nditioning units have been sold,\ncompared with 2.363 for those\ntwo months last year.\n\"Air conditioning first came\ninto the market in a substantial\nway In 1946.\" Mr. Hills pointed\nout. \"During that year there\nwere 1.200 sold in Washington.\nLast year 22.829 were sold.\nTotal sales to date from 1946\nthrough 1957 were 139,849.\n\"The new window air-condi\ntioners coming out will give re\nverse Cycle air-conditioning\nheat in winter and cooling in\nMUTUAL FUNdT~\nNCW TSU. april 77 r -NltitMl Asstcii\ntiN Stcarities Dnltri IK mm iMtaliees\nli< toil 111 llkll\nill'll Fee* I N 114 litl Sis F* 1.4? 114\natfnta FiM M 145 In Cl tan 117 112\ntalisitt IN 4?) In Tr Its I*4 IN\nla Mil 71 714 lU ItlllFlM 71 K 25 44\ntin